\int_{0}^{\infty}\exp(-x)dx
\int_{0}^{\infty}\exp(-x)dx=-\int_{0}^{1}\ln(t)dt
\int_0^\infty e^{-x}dx=:I
c>0
e^{-c}\leq e^{-x}\leq1 \ \ (0\leq x\leq c)
1-e^{-c}
c\to 0+
I=\int_0^c e^{-x}dx +\int_c^\infty e^{-x}dx= \int_0^c e^{-x}dx + e^{-c} I
(1-e^{-c}) I =\int_0^c e^{-x}dx\ .
c \ e^{-c} \leq (1-e^{-c}) I \leq c\ .
